      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers low, and so does my spirit. He has taken everything—my heart, my honor, my very reason for seeing the dawn. I feel as though I am but a ghost already, drifting through these cold, hollow halls. There is no light left in this world for one so broken. It would be so much quieter, wouldn't it? To just... cease. To let the shadows take me so I don't have to feel this ache anymore.",
